Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.95,0:04:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(642.04,682.16)}We're done for!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.99,0:04:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. There's still a way out.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.58,0:04:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to all become delinquents.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.50,0:04:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.08,0:04:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.29,0:04:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They get married early, without exception.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.84,0:04:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Without. Exception.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.01,0:04:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.92,0:04:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad kids get married early!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.51,0:04:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}My neighbour, Ku, is a real bad sort, \Nand she got married at fifteen!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.97,0:04:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you can't get married until sixteen?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:49.06,0:04:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the real deal.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.52,0:04:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.43,0:04:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, exactly.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.10,0:04:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The M*ld Maid infection and \Nthe delinquency cancel each other out.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.90,0:04:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.90,0:05:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But you can't just become \Na delinquent out of nowhere!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.28,0:05:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.15,0:05:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We beg of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.11,0:05:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.95,0:05:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Teach us your ways!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.99,0:05:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why me?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.99,0:05:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't no bloody delinquent and I never have been!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.51,0:05:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be our boss!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.75,0:05:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,B-Boss?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.00,0:05:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That has a certain wonderful ring to it...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.50,0:05:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Marii had always liked the sound of the word "boss".
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.14,0:05:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.80,0:05:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.43,0:05:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.26,0:05:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.89,0:05:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She's into it now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.06,0:05:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Well, what do you do? For starters, \Nc'mere and squat down, you bunch of lowlifes.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.94,0:05:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're already here!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.19,0:05:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we going to become delinquents?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.61,0:05:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll start with your looks!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.90,0:05:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We really look the part!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.53,0:05:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.86,0:05:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Omelet... and rice?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.32,0:05:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. They love using fancy typography to spell stuff.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.33,0:05:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup, and we've already made it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.84,0:05:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Check it out.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.00,0:05:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii Buratei.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.21,0:06:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Tetora Bouhatei.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.75,0:06:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Gankyou Kuurubiyuutei.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.17,0:06:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kigurumi Haroukitei.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.13,0:06:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kukuru Anrakutei.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.76,0:06:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's only the beginning.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.47,0:06:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}From now on, we'll only be using \Nfancy fonts and styling when speaking.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.34,0:06:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, forget words and focus on action.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.95,0:06:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to school at night and clean the windows!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.14,0:06:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Clean the windows?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.71,0:06:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Delinquents clean windows! \NWe don't only do bad.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.38,0:06:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I was wondering, are there \Nany legends among delinquents?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.17,0:06:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Legends?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.09,0:06:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Delinquents have lots of legends!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.30,0:06:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She's into it again.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.72,0:06:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Legends as cool as the Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.26,0:06:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the Legend of the Galactic Heroes?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.70,0:06:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not gonna be {\i1}that{\i0} awesome.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.52,0:07:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Delinquents aren't really on the "galactic" level. \NMore like the "local" level.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.36,0:07:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Lunar Legend Tsukihime?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.52,0:07:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the legend of King Arthuria?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.15,0:07:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}These people exist in opposition \Nto the forces of crazy fandoms.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.24,0:07:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Their legends don't hold a candle to ours.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.66,0:07:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I'm gonna create the Legend of Marii!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.95,0:07:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Long ago, there was a cross-dressing boy called Gold Marii.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.79,0:07:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Gold Marii spent every day lying around and doing nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.36,0:07:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Fin.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.21,0:07:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's folktale!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.69,0:07:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Folktales and fairy tales can get a little surreal sometimes.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.13,0:07:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That was more than surreal!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.59,0:07:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No story, no punchline, no point.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.68,0:07:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Legends are legends, \Nand folktales are a collection of legends.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.85,0:07:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking for delinquent-style legends, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.94,0:07:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What about this?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.44,0:07:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,At your part-time job, you and a friend quietly...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.32,0:07:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No! That's out of line!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.03,0:07:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My blog would blow up!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.61,0:07:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd get doxxed!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.16,0:07:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd call the school about it!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.66,0:07:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Even if we become delinquents, \Nthere's no guarantee we'll get married early.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.37,0:08:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of it another way.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.21,0:08:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This room is a box.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.62,0:08:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dolls are already put away.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.38,0:08:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. You're smart.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.46,0:08:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've been put away too.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.63,0:08:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We're kept women!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.80,0:08:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Kept women?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.84,0:08:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Marii liked the sound of being a kept woman.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.97,0:08:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew, that time already?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.81,0:08:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to go home.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.60,0:08:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We missed the last train.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.10,0:08:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii, you staying here?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.06,0:08:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Kept women don't leave their humble abodes.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.11,0:08:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.75,0:08:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just barge in!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.29,0:08:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At least knock!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.21,0:08:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Marii, a kept woman and a shut-in \Nare not the same thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.09,0:08:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a surreal take on a hina doll.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.47,0:08:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Still no Emperor doll to go with her, though.
Comment: 0,0:08:57.93,0:08:57.93,Default,chapter,0,0,0,,{Part B}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.18,0:09:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsukiji fish market!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.60,0:09:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Fish!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.15,0:09:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Tuna!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.77,0:09:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She certainly is cheerful.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.69,0:09:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We artists are late risers. \NEarly mornings don't agree with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.90,0:09:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Help! Kukuru isn't breathing!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.78,0:09:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So... tired...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.24,0:09:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you fall asleep, you'll die!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.53,0:09:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,320)}If sleeping means death, keep your eyes open!
Dialogue: 11,0:09:20.74,0:09:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(320,0)}Live tuna! Live tuna!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.33,0:09:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna eat live tuna!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.00,0:09:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii, a bluefin tuna weighs at least four hundred kilos.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.25,0:09:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And costs at least a million yen.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.46,0:09:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll rip it apart with my bare hands! Live on stage!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.71,0:09:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ocean-caught fish are flash-frozen at minus sixty degrees.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.18,0:09:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Catchy catchy fishy fishy!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.30,0:09:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you catch the cheaper it gets!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.51,0:09:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,She's annoying.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:42.47,0:09:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}As annoying as those foreign tourists who barge into \Nthe fish auctions, mess with the wares, and take pictures.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.65,0:09:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that really gets my goat. {## too obscure an expression perhaps?}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.11,0:09:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna go at them with a t*na cleaver.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.28,0:09:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If there were any justice, \Nthey'd get the Tsesarevich-Otsu treatment. {\Nthey'd be treated like the Tsesarevich was at Otsu.}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.78,0:09:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd cause an international incident!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.45,0:10:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Woohoo! Come to mama, tuna!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.08,0:10:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Marii even slept since yesterday?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.00,0:10:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why she's so highly strung.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.04,0:10:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But rules are rules!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.63,0:10:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These auctions are what the market's all about.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.34,0:10:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The old guys have such hoarse voices.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.01,0:10:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the top three gravelly voices.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.97,0:10:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Three? What are the other two?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.27,0:10:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.69,0:10:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ticket scalpers
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.85,0:10:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and His Excellency Rozen!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:29.85,0:10:32.82,Alt,,0,0,0,,{\an7\fs32\shad0\pos(33.333,18.667)}Note:
Dialogue: 9,0:10:29.85,0:10:32.82,Alt,,0,0,0,,{\an7\fs29.333\bord2.667\shad0\pos(33.333,52)}Former Prime Minister Taro Aso, \Nwho was reportedly seen reading \N"Rozen Maiden" at an airport.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.31,0:10:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Unbelievable!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.78,0:10:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Their gestures are pretty cool, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.99,0:10:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the top three gestures.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.66,0:10:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the other two?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.78,0:10:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Rappers
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.99,0:10:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and old men offering to buy their colleagues a drink at a bar.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.79,0:10:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the older guys who work here are kind of cool.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.12,0:10:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! An electric truck!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.79,0:10:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.02,0:10:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:54.67,0:10:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't fall in love!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.38,0:10:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Don't let it lead you astray \Nor give you the wrong idea!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.17,0:11:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Winter ski slopes, summer beaches, \Nschool uniforms, and electric trucks!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.80,0:11:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed. She's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.41,0:11:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When you come back to the drab old city,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.56,0:11:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}that guy never looks as hot as he did \Non the slopes or at the beach.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.43,0:11:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Or when he changes out of his uniform \Nand his normal clothes are beyond unfashionable.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.31,0:11:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Or when he steps off the electric truck \Nand he's just some old guy.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.94,0:11:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still some old guy even on the truck.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.61,0:11:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.44,0:11:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Those trucks are great. I understand wanting to ride one.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.53,0:11:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You need a full license to drive one.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.57,0:11:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What, surely a scooter license is enough?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.45,0:11:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for 50cc's!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.12,0:11:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I'd love to drive something like \Na Lamborghini Countach LP 500S,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.34,0:11:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}or maybe a De Tomaso Panthera \Nor a Porsche Carrera 2 Turbo.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.72,0:11:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something about supercars.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.79,0:11:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd prefer one of those lifting hoists.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.42,0:11:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughing ghosts?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.22,0:11:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A crane like they use to build apartment blocks.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.59,0:11:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd get chills up there.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.01,0:11:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.26,0:11:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I bet the breeze is really refreshing!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.52,0:11:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I'd get chills thinking about what \Nthey'd do if I dropped an iron bar on them.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.48,0:11:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-That's chilly...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.07,0:11:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,More like cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.69,0:11:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, Kigu?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.65,0:12:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Me? I wanna drive a Merc!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.41,0:12:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I want to go to a theme park and pay \Na hundred yen to ride the panda bear!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.33,0:12:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Cutie-pie!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.50,0:12:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our Kigu!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.54,0:12:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ugh, I'm sick of playing into their expectations of me.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.63,0:12:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Apparently a thousand grams of bonito flakes \Ncosts seven thousand yen.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.67,0:12:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why people come here.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.05,0:12:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You wouldn't normally buy one kilogram \Nof bonito flakes. You couldn't!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.80,0:12:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hup, there we go.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.36,0:12:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But she is.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.47,0:12:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Don't think you're getting any.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.06,0:12:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How many cats do you own?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:29.60,0:12:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They just looked good. I couldn't help myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.60,0:12:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Big changes are coming to the Outer Market.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.19,0:12:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, because of the move to Toyosu?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.69,0:12:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm way too used to "Tsukiji Market".
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.98,0:12:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Toyosu Market" just sounds weird.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.49,0:12:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The big fish market wasn't in Tsukiji originally.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.99,0:12:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was at Nihonbashi.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.49,0:12:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It moved due to the Great Kanto Earthquake.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.99,0:12:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Last time was tectonics, this time it's politics.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.08,0:12:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! A T-shirt with "Tuna" on it!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.92,0:12:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The kanji for that is written with "fish" and "exist".
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.44,0:13:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's to show how important it is...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.80,0:13:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Yeah! Like, you'd never have a word \Nwith "fish" and "doesn't exist," right?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.34,0:13:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But you could use that to mean \N"glass catfish", couldn't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.18,0:13:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.10,0:13:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}An aquarium fish that's completely \Ntransparent apart from its bones.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.10,0:13:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you use "illusion", it should mean "baby eel".
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.62,0:13:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where they're born is a long-standing mystery.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.40,0:13:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Apparently, they've even caught them \Nin the Mariana Trench.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.23,0:13:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle wrote that they're born spontaneously from mud.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.32,0:13:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they should use the symbol for "mud"!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.74,0:13:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I've no idea why eel uses "wide".
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.53,0:13:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What about just writing out "blue".
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.78,0:13:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how Mister explained the kanji for "mackerel".
Dialogue: 9,0:13:30.78,0:13:32.83,Alt,,0,0,0,,{\an7\fs32\shad0\pos(33.333,18.667)}Note:
Dialogue: 9,0:13:30.78,0:13:32.83,Alt,,0,0,0,,{\an7\fs29.333\bord2.667\shad0\pos(33.333,52)}Shigeo Nagashima, a very famous \Nbaseball player and manager.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.16,0:13:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue?! In English?!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.50,0:13:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese not good enough, eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.96,0:13:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's Mister's shtick.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:39.29,0:13:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You could combine "person" \Nand "strange" to get "Mister".
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.05,0:13:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Or "person" and "super"!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:44.05,0:13:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"Exceed" would work too.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.72,0:13:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii would be "person" and "butt".
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.72,0:13:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.51,0:13:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Person" and "thin skin"? "Delinquent"?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.22,0:13:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of those suck!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.35,0:13:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Kigu, you'd be "person" and "pure".
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.39,0:13:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yay!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.19,0:13:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think "cutie" would work too.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.15,0:14:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy! I'll work hard to be pure and cute!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.78,0:14:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ugh, I'm so sick of playing into their expectations of me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.11,0:14:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Kukuru would be "person" and...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.99,0:14:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"Pain" for sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.70,0:14:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.37,0:14:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's cool!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.37,0:14:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Born into a poor family, abused, neglected, \Nsent out to pick pockets on the street,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.00,0:14:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}protective custody, drop out, \Nteenage pregnancy, get married,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.25,0:14:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,domestic violence, poisoning, arrest, divorce, illness!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.71,0:14:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk about a sob story!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.01,0:14:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're trying to win a TV talent show!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.22,0:14:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Do me, do me! "Circle"?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.43,0:14:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What about "eight"?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.80,0:14:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"Person" plus "eight"?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.18,0:14:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"Person" plus eight. The numeral.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.47,0:14:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because of the glasses?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.10,0:14:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Even better, an infinity symbol!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.27,0:14:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just eight on its side!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.77,0:14:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What about me, I wonder?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.87,0:14:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're pretty neutral...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.86,0:14:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"Person" plus a square.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.28,0:14:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A square?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.99,0:14:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you can put whatever you like in it.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.70,0:14:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Like "rose", "azure", or "azalea".
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.45,0:14:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems a bit unfinished.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.66,0:14:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget unfinished, I'm famished!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.83,0:14:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get some lunch.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.62,0:15:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}What do you fancy? Sushi? \NOr some kind of set menu?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.54,0:15:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When you come to Tsukiji, it's gotta be Yoshinoya!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.42,0:15:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Beef bowl? Not fish?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.92,0:15:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The first Yoshinoya was established here in Tsukiji.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.59,0:15:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.89,0:15:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! The promised land!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.68,0:15:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait for me!
Comment: 0,0:15:22.86,0:15:22.86,Default,chapter,0,0,0,,{Part C}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:29.86,0:15:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Kukuru?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.11,0:15:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The manager just chewed me out.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.74,0:15:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}He said the electricity bill for the backstage room \Nwas unbelievably high last month.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.13,0:15:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Are there even that many appliances \Nin here that eat up electricity?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.72,0:15:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Well, maybe there are, but I don't get why \Nhe'd suddenly care about it now.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.76,0:15:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Save electricity, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.72,0:16:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no excuse for wasting it!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.43,0:16:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unkind to Mother Earth!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.39,0:16:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna search high and low to find the cause!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.19,0:16:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, I was thinking...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.11,0:16:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't the floor strangely warm?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.57,0:16:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.95,0:16:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gotta be underfloor heating!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.53,0:16:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving it on all the time is bad!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.20,0:16:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though they're tatami mats?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.62,0:16:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one way to find out!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.38,0:16:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No underfloor heating, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.05,0:16:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.59,0:16:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing unusual there.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.73,0:16:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... I have the feeling there actually \N{\i1}was{\i0} something unusual down there.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.47,0:16:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that uses electricity?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.48,0:16:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, no, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.39,0:16:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there was nothing unusual.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.06,0:16:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.61,0:16:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop fussing about trivial things!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.48,0:16:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta focus on the electricity bill!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.15,0:16:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! That's what's important!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.40,0:16:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Otherwise it'll be rolling blackouts! \NPrice increases! Shareholder lawsuits!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.66,0:16:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.28,0:17:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That reminds me, there have been \Nvoices coming from the walls recently.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.75,0:17:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,From the walls?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:03.30,0:17:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Voices?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.21,0:17:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! There must be speakers hidden in the walls!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.51,0:17:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Like JBL or Tannoy?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.84,0:17:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving music on all the time is bad!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.43,0:17:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one way to find out!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.19,0:17:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No speakers, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.32,0:17:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:32.99,0:17:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing unusual there.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:37.16,0:17:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, didn't you notice anything unusual there?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.45,0:17:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that uses electricity?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.58,0:17:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No, nothing that uses electricity, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.04,0:17:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, then there was nothing unusual.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.58,0:17:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, um, I mean—
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.17,0:17:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\q2}Can't these guys see anything \Nbut what they're focused on?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.80,0:17:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That reminds me.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.72,0:18:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The ceiling's been shaking recently.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.10,0:18:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaking?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.26,0:18:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe someone's using a massage chair on the other side.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.56,0:18:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,These days, massage chairs massage everything,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.64,0:18:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}from your shoulders to your back, \Nfrom your calves to your arms.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.90,0:18:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So they use a lot of electricity.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.69,0:18:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one way to find out!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.91,0:18:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No massage chair, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.74,0:18:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.66,0:18:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing unusual there.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.16,0:18:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I feel like there might have been \Na mortal danger lurking in the ceiling...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.63,0:18:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that uses electricity?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.84,0:18:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, no, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.88,0:18:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, then there was nothing unusual.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.38,0:18:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.59,0:18:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}So there weren't any electrical appliances \Nunder the floor, in the walls, or in the ceiling.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.39,0:18:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that means the problem must be in the room.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.81,0:18:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.10,0:18:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Your glasses!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.06,0:18:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with 'em?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.31,0:18:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They act like a scouter, consuming a \Nsupercomputer's worth of electricity, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.48,0:18:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.19,0:18:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Why would I need a scouter to confirm \Nthat your power level is basically zero?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.83,0:19:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}When it comes to saving electricity, \Nevery little bit helps.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.32,0:19:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that even relevant?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.03,0:19:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, guys.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.79,0:19:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you reckon saving electricity is a bit unambitious?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.00,0:19:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Rather than cutting down how much we use, \Nshouldn't we instead focus on generating more?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.46,0:19:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a human-powered generator!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.17,0:19:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's gonna ride it?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.59,0:19:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.72,0:19:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Definitely Marii.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.88,0:19:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Marii's idea.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.05,0:19:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, fine! I'll do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.76,0:19:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You miss one hundred percent of the volts you don't make!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.41,0:19:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this really producing electricity?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.73,0:19:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a socket...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.61,0:19:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's weaker than a bicycle light.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.61,0:19:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Less power than an AA battery.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.12,0:19:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Saw that coming.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.33,0:19:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh... that hurt...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.37,0:19:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.08,0:19:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If we don't patch this up, \Nthe manager'll be even angrier with us!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.71,0:20:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Wasn't that some kinda human-shaped thing there?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.68,0:20:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that got to do with generating electricity?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.26,0:20:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Your method isn't enough for modern times.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.76,0:20:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There are more efficient and high-tech solutions.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.69,0:20:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Solar and wind aren't working at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.73,0:20:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, ofcourse. We're inside.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.15,0:20:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The sun's out of the question, \Nbut can't we get some wind going?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:18.65,0:20:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Wind makes me think of...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.88,0:20:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, the wind blew.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.34,0:20:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They say the wind blows when \Nfated lovers meet for the first time!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.80,0:20:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.84,0:20:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not all!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.76,0:20:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They say that when you have \Nan instant connection with someone...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.90,0:20:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,there's electricity!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.86,0:20:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.61,0:20:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}So to create electricity, \Nwe need to create encounters.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.78,0:21:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.15,0:21:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in, come in! We have lots of pretty girls!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.45,0:21:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's working! I can practically \N{\i1}feel{\i0} the electricity in the air!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.46,0:21:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Police! Nobody move!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:16.29,0:21:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We received a tip-off that there were \Nunlicensed indecent activities going on here!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.00,0:21:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Indecent? We're just trying to \Nmake a little electricity here!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:21.84,0:21:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're digging yourself deeper!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.96,0:21:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop being so obstinate!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.15,0:21:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What on earth...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.19,0:21:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was you who used all that electricity, Kigu.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:47.41,0:21:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But... what?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.37,0:21:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels good to solve that mystery.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.70,0:21:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm glad.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.37,0:21:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopefully the manager won't get mad at us again.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.79,0:21:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.06,0:21:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just the robot.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:57.67,0:22:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}At that moment, the real Kigu was asleep \Nat home, dreaming of electric sheep.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.17,0:22:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Two's enough... please understand...
Comment: 0,0:23:39.94,0:23:39.94,Default,chapter,0,0,0,,{Preview}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:40.52,0:23:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Kukuru Anrakutei here.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.10,0:23:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Summer is the season of love, \Nand fall is the season of sports.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:47.44,0:23:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of season would you say winter is?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.53,0:23:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the season of broken hearts and injuries.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.24,0:23:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Better to stay indoors and stay safe.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.08,0:24:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Winter is the season of hibernation.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.29,0:24:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Rakugo Girls episode 8 includes:
Dialogue: 10,0:24:04.22,0:24:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"Bag of Gold", "Unsteady", and "Is It Over Yet?"
